#Purging Scythe (#1085): at my upkeep it deals 2 to the creature with least toughness.
#The 2/2 bears (lowest vs the 3/3 giant) die at my next upkeep.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
inplay:purging scythe,hill giant
[PLAYER2]
inplay:grizzly bears
[DO]
goto end
goto firstmain
goto end
goto upkeep
choice 0
goto upkeep
goto upkeep
[ASSERT]
UPKEEP
[PLAYER1]
inplay:purging scythe,hill giant
[PLAYER2]
graveyard:grizzly bears
[END]
#PARKED - the trigger FIRES (StackAbility resolves at my upkeep) but the damage never
#lands. Not the frozen-criterion problem (parse-time value 2 also matches the bears):
#the trigger-context `damage:2 notaTarget(creature[...])` auto-pick resolves without
#choosing anything - a TRIGGER-side cousin of the lost-chooser family (the v2/v3
#spell-context wrap doesn't apply to triggers). The toughness dynamic-criterion
#plumbing (mirroring #1125's manacost fix) was added anyway - correct in principle.
